The first square below is in position $ABCD$. After rotating the square $90^\circ$ clockwise about its center point, the second square is in position $DABC$, as shown. Next, square $DABC$ is reflected over its vertical line of symmetry, resulting in the third square in position $CBAD$. If the pattern of alternately rotating $90^\circ$ clockwise and reflecting over the vertical line of symmetry continues, in what position will the $2007$th square be? Write your answer starting with the lower left vertex and continuing clockwise with the other three vertices. Do not use spaces or commas when entering your answer.$$ egin{align*} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) rectangle (2,2);\draw (3,0) rectangle (5,2);\draw (6,0) rectangle (8,2);
ode at (0.3,0.3) {A};
ode at (0.3,1.7) {B};
ode at (1.7,1.7) {C};
ode at (1.7,0.3) {D};
ode at (3.3,0.3) {D};
ode at (3.3,1.7) {A};
ode at (4.7,1.7) {B};
ode at (4.7,0.3) {C};
ode at (6.3,0.3) {C};
ode at (6.3,1.7) {B};
ode at (7.7,1.7) {A};
ode at (7.7,0.3) {D};
ode at (1,2.3) {1st square};
ode at (4,2.3) {2nd square};  
ode at (7,2.3) {3rd square};\end{tikzpicture}\end{align*}$$

A wooden model of a square pyramid has a base edge of 12 cm and an altitude of 8 cm. A cut is made parallel to the base of the pyramid that separates it into two pieces: a smaller pyramid and a frustum. Each base edge of the smaller pyramid is 6 cm and its altitude is 4 cm. The task is to find the volume of the frustum in cubic centimeters. egin{center} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (4,0) -- (2,3) -- cycle;\draw (0,0) -- (2,1.5);\draw (4,0) -- (2,1.5);\draw[dashed] (1,0) -- (3,0) -- (2,1.5) -- cycle;
ode at (2,-0.5) {12 cm};
ode at (4.5,1.5) {8 cm};
ode at (1.5,0.75) {6 cm};
ode at (3.5,0.75) {4 cm};\end{tikzpicture}\end{center}
